some like it hot is a 1939 comedy film starring bob hope , shirley ross , and gene krupa . the movie was directed by george archainbaud , and the screenplay was written by wilkie c. mahoney and lewis r. foster , based on the play the great magoo by ben hecht and gene fowler , which performed briefly on broadway in 1932 . the film was released the year before road to singapore converted theatre and radio star hope into a huge movie box office draw . legendary cinematographer karl &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; filmed the movie . the title of the film is taken from a nursery rhyme , and bears no relation to billy wilder 's acclaimed 1959 comedy film some like it hot starring marilyn monroe , jack lemmon , and tony curtis . the movie was reissued for television as rhythm romance , presumably to avoid viewers confusing it with the other some like it hot .